# shell-env_example — shell environment sourced before each wake firing.
#
# Copy to "shell-env" in the kanban root and edit:
#
#   cp shell-env_example "$PGAI_AGENT_KANBAN_ROOT_PATH/shell-env"
#
# This file is shell-sourced by wake_common.sh. Put PATH adjustments,
# virtualenv activation, and any other non-secret shell environment here.
# For sensitive credentials (OAuth tokens, API keys), use "secrets" instead
# — see secrets_example.
#
# Notes:
#   - This file is OPTIONAL — wake scripts work without it as long as the
#     cron environment inherits a usable PATH and KANBAN_ROOT is exported
#     from the operator's ~/.bashrc or equivalent.
#   - The file is shell-sourced — any syntax error halts the wake firing.
#     Test edits with: bash -n $PGAI_AGENT_KANBAN_ROOT_PATH/shell-env
#   - For wake-loop tunables (max_tasks_per_wake, etc.), edit kanban.cfg
#     [wake] instead. For per-agent model overrides, edit kanban.cfg
#     [models.<provider>] (e.g., [models.claude], [models.codex]) — the
#     active provider is resolved from [providers] active at wake startup.
#     This file is shell-only — no INI translation happens here.
#
# All lines below are commented out by default. Uncomment to use.


# --- Kanban root (typically set in ~/.bashrc, but can live here) ---
# Cron jobs invoking the wake scripts need KANBAN_ROOT to find the
# installation. Most operators set this once in their ~/.bashrc; you can
# also set it here so the wake script is self-contained.
# No default — required for any cron-driven operation.
#
# export PGAI_AGENT_KANBAN_ROOT_PATH="$HOME/pgai_agent_kanban"
# export KANBAN_ROOT_PATH="$PGAI_AGENT_KANBAN_ROOT_PATH"


# --- PATH ---
# Cron jobs run with a minimal PATH and won't find tools in $HOME without
# this. Uncomment if `claude` or `codex` CLIs aren't on the default cron PATH.
# Default: not modified (uses whatever PATH cron provides)
# export PATH="$HOME/.local/bin:$HOME/bin:$PATH"


# --- Python virtualenv (optional) ---
# Activate a Python virtualenv if your system Python is too old.
# pm_materialize.py and pm_status.py require Python 3.10+.
# No default — leave commented unless system Python is unsuitable.
# source "$HOME/py3.12/bin/activate"


# --- Other ---
# export EDITOR=vim

